      <h1 class='title'>Oversight Commissioner's Report</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 April 2004 vol 420 c37WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_37ws' title='Col. 37WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 April 2004 vol 420 c37WS' name='column_37ws' href='#column_37ws' rel='bookmark'>37WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0420P2_20040427_CWS_2'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-ian-pearson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0420P2_20040427_CWS_2' title='Link to this speech by Mr Ian Pearson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-ian-pearson" title="Mr Ian Pearson">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Northern Ireland (Mr. Ian Pearson)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I have today laid before this House a copy of the oversight commissioner's first statutory report for the year 2004, which is being published today, in accordance with section 68(4)(a) of the <a href="/acts/police-northern-ireland-act-2000">Police (Northern Ireland) Act 2000</a>.</p><p>This is the first report compiled by Al Hutchinson as oversight commissioner and the 10th in the series of oversight reports published since 2001.</p><p>I would like to take this opportunity to welcome the new oversight commissioner to this very important post.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
